The construction of ClearSecurityCacheRequest object happens on the client side. We might have validation for its parameters on the server side, but the caller has to hard code the "api_key" value in the client code. Something like:
public final class ClearSecurityCacheRequest implements Validatable {

    enum CacheName {
        API_KEY
    }

    private final CacheName cacheName;

would help a bit.
A separate request object type would still be preferable IMO.

